<l>vēṟṟumai yalvaḻi yāyta mākum</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>[Words] ending in the sound <foreign xml:lang="ta">-v</foreign> and commencing with demonstratives</l>
<l>behave as when followed by case-markers, as explained above.<note
              place="foot">i.e. <foreign xml:lang="ta">av</foreign> ' those things ', <foreign
                xml:lang="ta">iv</foreign> ' these things ', <foreign xml:lang="ta">uv</foreign> '
          those [intermediate] things ' get the empty morph <foreign xml:lang="ta">vaṟṟu</foreign>
          (cf. Nos. 134, 184) : e.g. <foreign xml:lang="ta">av + talai &gt; avaṟṟuttalai</foreign> '
          the head of those things '.</note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
